text:
East 4th Street, north side, west from (No. 35-31, garage), a point midway between the Bowery and Lafayette Street, and to the latter (left). The 3½-story structure with dormer windows is the "Old Merchants House" built by Seabury Tredwell in 1836 and occupied by him and his spinster daughters until 1930. It is now a historical museum, under the auspices of the Historic Landmark Society. For a full account see the New York Times, Sunday May 3, 1936.

December 9, 1937.

George D. Chinn.
